| Location                                            | Level 6–9 of [Gehennom](/wiki/Gehennom "Gehennom") |
| [Bones](/wiki/Bones "Bones")                        | Yes                                                |
| [Mappable](/wiki/Magic_mapping "Magic mapping")     | Yes                                                |

[SpliceHack](/wiki/SpliceHack "SpliceHack") changes the layout of [Baalzebub's Lair](/wiki/Baalzebub%27s_Lair "Baalzebub's Lair"), surrounding it with a swamp.[\[1\]](#cite_note-1) This layout appears to be based on the [Lethe patch](/wiki/Gehennom_\(Lethe_patch\)#Baalzebub.27s_lair "Gehennom (Lethe patch)").

[Baalzebub](/wiki/Baalzebub "Baalzebub") [&](/wiki/Baalzebub "Baalzebub"), a [ghost](/wiki/Ghost "Ghost") , a [horned devil](/wiki/Horned_devil "Horned devil") [&](/wiki/Horned_devil "Horned devil") and a [barbed devil](/wiki/Barbed_devil "Barbed devil") [&](/wiki/Barbed_devil "Barbed devil") are in the central complex at the positions shown above.

Additionally the following are scattered randomly around the level:

- four random pieces of [armor](/wiki/Armor "Armor")
- four random [weapons](/wiki/Weapon "Weapon")
- three random [gems](/wiki/Gem "Gem") or [stones](/wiki/Stone "Stone")
- four random [potions](/wiki/Potions "Potions")
- four random [scrolls](/wiki/Scrolls "Scrolls")
- two [spiked pits](/wiki/Spiked_pit "Spiked pit")
- two [fire traps](/wiki/Fire_trap "Fire trap")
- two [sleeping gas traps](/wiki/Sleeping_gas_trap "Sleeping gas trap")
- two [anti-magic fields](/wiki/Anti-magic_field "Anti-magic field")
- three [rust traps](/wiki/Rust_trap "Rust trap")
- four [magic traps](/wiki/Magic_trap "Magic trap")
- a random [L](/wiki/Lich "Lich")
- two [ghosts](/wiki/Ghost "Ghost")
- one or two [shades](/wiki/Shade "Shade")
- two random [&](/wiki/%26 "&")
- three or four [horned devils](/wiki/Horned_devil "Horned devil")
- four or five [lemures](/wiki/Lemure "Lemure")
- three random [V](/wiki/Vampire "Vampire")
- three random [F](/wiki/F "F")
- a [green slime](/wiki/Green_slime "Green slime") named "Glurrz, emissary of [Juiblex](/wiki/Juiblex "Juiblex")"
- two or three random [P](/wiki/P "P")

All of the walls are non-diggable. Most of the level is unlit except the area around the upstair.

## Strategy

In theory, one could get through the level without a means of crossing water, by walking carefully on the solid floor tiles and opening the drawbridge with a [wand of opening](/wiki/Wand_of_opening "Wand of opening"). However that is not necessarily practical.
